    "body": "I've tried many different Cython versions from 0.28 up to the latest master with Python 2.7.16. All have the same problem. The following code:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncdef unicode decode_pdfdocencoding(str byte_array) except+:\r\n    cdef Py_UNICODE c\r\n    cdef const unsigned char[:] byte_array_view = byte_array\r\n    cdef Py_UNICODE *mvpdfDocEncodingU = &_pdfDocEncodingU.data.as_pyunicodes[0]\r\n    cdef unicode retval\r\n    retval = u' ' * byte_array_view.shape[0]\r\n    for i in range(byte_array_view.shape[0]):\r\n        c = mvpdfDocEncodingU[byte_array_view[i]]\r\n        if c == u'\\u0000':\r\n            raise UnicodeDecodeError(\"pdfdocencoding\", byte_array[i], -1, -1, \"does not exist in translation table\")\r\n        retval[i] = c  # <-- BUG: Cython produces: None = __pyx_v_c;\r\n    return retval\r\n```\r\n\r\nCython produces 'None = __pyx_v_c;' for 'retval[i] = c.\r\n",
