        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "`unicode` (and `str`) are immutible so you shouldn't be writing to them. You maybe should be using C-API functions to manipulate the unicode string here: `PyUnicode_WRITE` on a string created with `PyUnicode_New` (so that you're sure it's genuinely a new string and not an interned one)?\r\n\r\nI think Cython should fail with a compile error rather than generating invalid code, so it is a bug",
